Havotron turned to Scrapper.  "Have you gotten a reply yet?"

"No,Sir!" Scrapper replied back.  Again he turned to the radio 
transmitter, and over the galactic default for Deceptcon receivers. 
"This is Scrapper of the D.E.D.  My, leader Havotron has been sent to 
take control. He orders a meeting between our faction and yours to 
discuss the future leadership.  Please reply ASAP."

"Ok another message sent my lord. "

"Good!"
0-------------------------------------------------------------------0


Quake arrived at the top of the tunnel his engine smoking.  "Shit, it 
burrrrnnnnssss....."  Tiptop jumped out of the inside of the tank 
gasping for air.  Heater was right behind him.  As they jumped out 
bellows of smoke poured out of his tank cockpit.  Tiptop jumped to the 
back and with a heave of strength lifted the tank up.  "Haha" he cried 
out.  "I still have my circus strength."

Heater looked to him.  "Yea, and the brains."  the ex street punk 
crawled under the tank and looked around for a bit.  Being a street wise 
punk he new how to do anything on vehicles, and quickly.  In a couple 
minutes he was out and Tiptop dropped Quake's back end down.

Heater looked at him.  "Quake you melted your transmission again, 
luckily I patched it up nice and good. Now lets go." The two nebulans 
jumped back into the tank and Quake drove off.

Quake spoke to Apeface.  "Do you have any readings monkeyface on the 
salthater."  Quake gave out a chuckle thinking his pointless jokes funny.

Dreadwind flew out of the cave housing the D.E.D base. Darkwing 
followed.  "All right lets join and get this over with.  " The two 
joined creating a super jet and blasted of to the East.
